      "end": 19.98,
      "text": "The",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-001",
      "start": 19.98,
      "end": 21.46,
      "text": "Donkelberg.com.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-002",
      "start": 26.16,
      "end": 29.22,
      "text": "Aesop's Fables. The Black Amore.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-003",
      "start": 31.28,
      "end": 39.98,
      "text": "A man once bought an Ethiopian slave, who had a black skin like all Ethiopians, but his new master",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-004",
      "start": 40.56,
      "end": 49.34,
      "text": "thought his color was due to his late owners having neglected him, and that all he wanted was a good scrubbing.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-005",
      "start": 49.34,
      "end": 57.42,
      "text": "So, he set to work with plenty of soap and hot water, and rubbed away at him with a will.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-006",
      "start": 58.3,
      "end": 68.46,
      "text": "But all to no purpose, for his skin remained as black as ever, while the poor wretch all but died from the cold he caught.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-007",
      "start": 69.68,
      "end": 72.28,
      "text": "End of The Black Amore.",
      "note": ""
    }
  ],
